===========================================================================

# To install uv, see below.

uv python install --default
# To see which versions are available:
uv python list

===========================================================================

# uv

# Install uv (don't use `sudo`):
curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh

# To update uv:
uv self update

`uv` is "A single tool to replace pip, pip-tools, pipx, poetry, pyenv, twine, virtualenv, and more."

# As of 2025-10-31, I'm trying to avoid all use of pip and pipx.
pipx is for executables.
pip is for modules.

# As of 2025-05-11, this is a very old version.
# sudo apt -yqq install ruff

===========================================================================

UV

# I should build html5validator rather than installing the Python package.

# uv tool install mypy && \
uv tool install ruff && \
echo "success"
# To upgrade all tools:
uv tool upgrade --all

# For packages, install per-venv, not once and for all in the system as this would do.
# uv pip install --system \
#   ggplot \
#   loguru \
#   replicate \
#   rich && \
# echo "success"

===========================================================================

EXECUTABLES/APPLICATIONS

# When possible, it is better to do "uv add ... --dev" within a project.
# That does not currently work for ruff, but it does for all other tools.
uv tool install ruff
uv tool install ty
# I should build html5validator rather than installing the Python package.  (Why?)
uv tool install html5validator

----------------

# Older (don't use; use uv now):

# I should build html5validator rather than installing the Python package.

# At CSE, use `--user` and drop `sudo`.
sudo apt -y install pipx
sudo pipx install pip
pip install replicate --break-system-packages
sudo pip install mypy
# OR: python -m pip install mypy

# Each of these sometimes works and sometimes doesn't!
# pip install ruff
# pipx install ruff
# Alternative, if neither of the above works: pip install ruff --break-system-packages

