===========================================================================

MODULES/PACKAGES

# It's better to install them per-venv, using uv, not globally.

# Using Ubuntu:
sudo apt -qqy install python3-pandas python3-openai python3-yaml

sudo apt -y install pipx
sudo pip install ggplot
sudo pip install loguru
sudo pip install rich

----------------

# At CSE, always use --user flag:
pipx install --force --user ggplot black
pip install --upgrade --user requests

----------------

To review which packages can be upgraded/updated:
pipx install pip-review
pipx install --upgrade setuptools
# This gives lots of errors; do I need to pass --use-deprecated=backtrack-on-build-failures to "pip3 install"?
pip-review --interactive

===========================================================================

To install ipython, DON'T do
  sudo apt -yqq install ipython-notebook
which is an old version on Ubuntu.
Instead, do (use `sudo` if I have sudo rights):
  pipx install ipython --upgrade
  pipx install notebook --upgrade

But, in other cases the Ubuntu package works better than the pip package.

===========================================================================

Python 3:

# To install the latest Python version:
uv python install

----------------

# OLDER
VER=3.13.3
cd ~/bin/install
wget https://www.python.org/ftp/python/${VER}/Python-${VER}.tgz
tar xfz Python-${VER}.tgz
cd Python-${VER}
./configure --prefix=${HOME}/.local --enable-optimizations
make
# sudo make install
make install
(cd $HOME/.local/bin && ln -s python3 python)

# Test:
python-${VER} --version
## TODO: test that SSL works

===========================================================================

Python 2, which is no longer in the Debian/Ubuntu repositories:

cd ~/bin/install
wget https://www.python.org/ftp/python/2.7.9/Python-2.7.9.tgz
tar xzf Python-2.7.9.tgz
cd Python-2.7.9
./configure --prefix $HOME/bin/install/Python-2.7.9-install
make install
rm -f $HOME/bin/install/Python-2.7.9-install/bin/python

